name: Dr. Anthony J. Kohler
about:
Dr. Anthony J. Kohler is from Burlington, Wisconsin, a small town on the southeast corner of the state. He moved to sunny Arizona in 1986 and has been enjoying life here since then.

He completed his undergraduate degrees and dental school at the University of Minnesota and has continued his clinical education with hundreds of hours of courses in orthodontics, TMD / TMJ treatments, clinical dentistry, implantology and biological hollistic dentistry.

In addition, Dr. Kohler received a diploma in sleep apnea dentistry and is a member of the International Academy of Biological Dentistry and Medicine (IABDM).

He likes spending time with his son Karl, worshiping at church on Sundays, ATV off roading on weekends and looks forward to meeting you!

clinic.name: 24th Street Dental Biltmore
clinic.description:
24th Street Dental Biltmore's office sits just off East Indian School Road, home to restaurants, retail shops, and much more. We have patients from all over the greater Phoenix area, from Flagstaff to Tucson, we even have some patients from Beverly Hills and Dubai, but wherever you call home, know that your cosmetic dentist will welcome you like family. 

From our convenient parking lot to our friendly office staff, patients know they are in safe and gentle hands. Our waiting room is calm, clean, and comfortable, and our exam rooms, state-of-the-art. 24th Street Dental Biltmore takes pride in our practice and considers it an honor to treat you and your family. Schedule an appointment today and experience the difference! We use latest technology and dental equipment to make your visit with us as efficient and seamless as possible. 

If you're unhappy with the way your smile looks right now, you've landed in the perfect spot! Patients frequently desire to alter or correct cosmetic flaws they find unattractive. 24th Street Biltmore offers a range of treatments, ranging from minor adjustments to extensive repairs, that can enhance your smile. These procedures are effective in dealing with issues like chipped, misshapen, discolored, or even absent teeth. Apart from enhancing your experience, these procedures often resolve other oral health problems, such as an irregular bite. 

We in-network with Delta Premier and accept all PPO plans, HSAs and FSAs. We also have flexible payment plans available (eg 1yrs, 3yrs, 5yrs) so patients do not have to compromise their oral health in their time of need.
